-- Chilean Stock Movers: Cencosud, Copec and La Polar Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-06-08T21:30:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/chilean-stock-movers-cencosud-and-empresas-la-polar-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  rose 1.5 percent to 4,349.46, completing the
biggest weekly gain in almost four months. The  MSCI Chile index 
advanced 1.3 percent to 2,355.22.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD)   gained 2.7 percent to 2,849.3
pesos. Chile’s largest retailer by sales cut the amount of
shares it plans to offer in  New York  to 91.3 million from 125
million shares, according to a filing sent today to the
Securities & Exchange Commission.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)   increased 2.6 percent to
7,352.9 pesos. Celulosa Arauco & Constitucion SA, a unit of
Copec, agreed to pay $243 million for 100 percent of Canadian
wood panel producer Flakeboard Co.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   slid 2.5 percent to
384.61 pesos after surging 11 percent in the previous two days.
The department-store operator said billionaire Alvaro Saieh
hasn’t agreed to acquire all new shares it plans to sell and
acquire control of the company, denying a report published
yesterday in Santiago-based online newspaper El Mostrador.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
